00:51:47.541 --> 00:51:50.294 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our postcard this month is from a country

00:51:50.294 --> 00:51:54.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s been called the land of the volcanoes,
El Salvador.

00:51:54.882 --> 00:51:59.136 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of its 20 youngest volcanoes,
some are still active.

00:51:59.136 --> 00:52:01.138 line:90% position:50% align:center
The picturesque Lake Coatepeque

00:52:01.138 --> 00:52:03.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
was formed
when a group of volcanoes collapsed,

00:52:03.891 --> 00:52:07.103 line:90% position:50% align:center
allowing rainwater to fill the crater.

00:52:07.103 --> 00:52:10.314 line:90% position:50% align:center
Despite its mountainous terrain, El Salvador

00:52:10.314 --> 00:52:13.359 line:90% position:50% align:center
is known for its agriculture,
especially coffee.

00:52:14.443 --> 00:52:17.196 line:90% position:50% align:center
The fertile volcanic soil produces

00:52:17.196 --> 00:52:20.199 line:90% position:50% align:center
a highly sought-after coffee
known for its sweetness,

00:52:20.199 --> 00:52:24.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
notes of chocolate and caramel,
and gentle acidity.

00:52:25.287 --> 00:52:28.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
El Salvador
is Central America’s smallest country

00:52:28.499 --> 00:52:31.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
and also its most densely populated.

00:52:31.961 --> 00:52:33.963 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah’s Witnesses have been active

00:52:33.963 --> 00:52:37.675 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the country since
the first missionaries arrived in 1945.

00:52:38.592 --> 00:52:41.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
Those intrepid missionaries
faced the daunting task

00:52:41.846 --> 00:52:45.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
of declaring the good news
to roughly one and a half million people.

00:52:46.642 --> 00:52:50.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Salvadoran people
are kind and industrious,

00:52:50.187 --> 00:52:54.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
very hospitable,
and ready to talk about the Bible.

00:52:54.150 --> 00:52:55.860 line:90% position:50% align:center
Those first seeds

00:52:55.860 --> 00:52:59.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Kingdom truth grew rapidly, and in 1972,

00:52:59.780 --> 00:53:03.325 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah’s Witnesses gained legal recognition.

00:53:03.325 --> 00:53:07.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, the more than 37,000 publishers

00:53:07.038 --> 00:53:09.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
conduct almost 20,000 Bible studies.

00:53:09.915 --> 00:53:13.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
They preach in Spanish,
Salvadoran Sign Language,

00:53:13.919 --> 00:53:17.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Mandarin Chinese,
and they declare the good news to inmates

00:53:17.923 --> 00:53:19.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
in 20 different prisons.

00:53:21.260 --> 00:53:24.346 line:90% position:50% align:center
Nearly one in seven publishers
serves as a pioneer.

00:53:25.097 --> 00:53:26.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
This past service year saw

00:53:26.932 --> 00:53:31.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
more than a 20 percent increase
in total hours spent preaching.

00:53:32.063 --> 00:53:36.025 line:90% position:50% align:center
The brothers enjoy harbor witnessing
in the coastal town of Acajutla.

00:53:37.651 --> 00:53:39.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
The El Boqueron Congregation

00:53:39.445 --> 00:53:41.530 line:90% position:50% align:center
is located in the coffee-growing region

00:53:41.530 --> 00:53:44.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
of El Progreso La Libertad.

00:53:44.533 --> 00:53:47.119 line:90% position:50% align:center
After a delicious cup in the morning,

00:53:47.119 --> 00:53:50.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
the brothers walk from house to house
and farm to farm.

00:53:50.539 --> 00:53:52.458 line:90% position:50% align:center
They conduct on average

00:53:52.458 --> 00:53:55.836 line:90% position:50% align:center
50 Bible studies, and this past year,

00:53:55.836 --> 00:53:58.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
174 attended the Memorial.

00:53:59.590 --> 00:54:03.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
The 66 publishers
of the El Boqueron Congregation

00:54:03.302 --> 00:54:06.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
send their warm Christian love and affection.

